Find Requests Blocked by WAF for Today
You can filter records where action = 'BLOCK' and restrict the time range.

Query to Get Blocked Requests for Today:
sql
Copy
Edit
SELECT 
  timestamp,
  webaclid,
  terminatingruleid,
  httprequest.clientip,
  httprequest.uri
FROM waf_logs
WHERE action = 'BLOCK'
AND year = CAST(date_format(current_date, '%Y') AS STRING)
AND month = CAST(date_format(current_date, '%m') AS STRING)
AND day = CAST(date_format(current_date, '%d') AS STRING)
ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
How This Works:
‚úÖ current_date gets today's date dynamically.
‚úÖ date_format(current_date, '%Y') extracts the year as a string.
‚úÖ date_format(current_date, '%m') extracts the month as a string.
‚úÖ date_format(current_date, '%d') extracts the day as a string.
‚úÖ ORDER BY timestamp DESC sorts results from newest to oldest.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Find Blocked Requests in a Specific Time Range
To filter by a specific time range, we need to convert the timestamp field to the Chicago timezone.

Query for Blocked Requests Between 8 AM - 10 AM (Chicago Time)
sql
Copy
Edit
SELECT 
  timestamp,
  webaclid,
  terminatingruleid,
  httprequest.clientip,
  httprequest.uri,
  from_iso8601_timestamp(timestamp) AT TIME ZONE 'America/Chicago' AS chicago_time
FROM waf_logs
WHERE action = 'BLOCK'
AND year = CAST(date_format(current_date, '%Y') AS STRING)
AND month = CAST(date_format(current_date, '%m') AS STRING)
AND day = CAST(date_format(current_date, '%d') AS STRING)
AND from_iso8601_timestamp(timestamp) AT TIME ZONE 'America/Chicago' 
    BETWEEN TIMESTAMP '2025-03-11 08:00:00' AND TIMESTAMP '2025-03-11 10:00:00'
ORDER BY chicago_time DESC;
How This Works:
‚úÖ from_iso8601_timestamp(timestamp) AT TIME ZONE 'America/Chicago' converts UTC logs to Chicago time.
‚úÖ BETWEEN TIMESTAMP 'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS' AND TIMESTAMP 'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS' filters by a specific time range.
‚úÖ Adjust the date dynamically for automation.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Get All Logs with Chicago Time Conversion
If you want all logs (not just blocked requests) with timestamps converted to Chicago time, use:

sql
Copy
Edit
SELECT 
  timestamp,
  from_iso8601_timestamp(timestamp) AT TIME ZONE 'America/Chicago' AS chicago_time,
  webaclid,
  terminatingruleid,
  action,
  httprequest.clientip,
  httprequest.uri
FROM waf_logs
WHERE year = CAST(date_format(current_date, '%Y') AS STRING)
AND month = CAST(date_format(current_date, '%m') AS STRING)
AND day = CAST(date_format(current_date, '%d') AS STRING)
ORDER BY chicago_time DESC;
‚úÖ This query converts timestamps to Chicago time while retrieving all logs (BLOCK, ALLOW, COUNT, etc.).

Summary of Queries
Query	Description
1Ô∏è‚É£ Blocked requests today	Shows WAF BLOCK requests for today.
2Ô∏è‚É£ Blocked requests in a time range	Filters BLOCK logs between 8 AM - 10 AM CST/CDT.
3Ô∏è‚É£ All logs with Chicago time	Converts all timestamps to America/Chicago timezone.
